==References== {{Reflist}} ==External links== *[http://www.foot-base.com/en/CAF/Madagascar/ASF_Fianarantsoa/] *[http://scoreshelf.com/rmqb/en/ASF_Fianarantsoa/Champions_Cup] [[Category:Football clubs in Madagascar]] {{Madagascar-footyclub-stub}}

The '''Arabian Sea Country Club''' (A.S.C.C.L.), is a recreational club with a [[golf course]] and several other sporting facilities, located in [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]].
The Country Club is the collective result of a group of companies, spearheaded by former test cricketer [[Javed Burki]]. The 18 hole, par 72 golf course has been designed by ''K. Okada San'' of ''Taisei Corporation'' of [[Japan]]. The Clubhouse and other facilities were designed by Architect ''Asad I. A. Khan'' and constructed through the management of ''Zaeem Lutfi'' and ''FMCL''. The Arabian Sea Country Club has a [[golf course]] along with an elaborate Swimming Pool Complex, Sauna, Jacuzzi Steam bath and Fitness Centre. The club also has an international standard [[cricket ground]] which is currently used as a venue for some domestic matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/pakistan/content/ground/782275.html|work=Cricinfo|title=Arabian Sea Country Club}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nation.com.pk/karachi/04-Oct-2009/Arabian-Sea-Club-to-unveil-cricket-stadium-today|title=Arabian Sea Club to unveil cricket stadium today|work=The Nation|date=4 October 2009|accessdate=5 May 2015}}</ref>
