'''Israel Cycling Academy''' (''[[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]] team code:'' '''ICA''') is a UCI Pro Continental team founded in 2015 and based in [[Israel]]. It participates in [[UCI Continental Circuits]] races.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/team/Cycling_Academy_Team_2015|title=Cycling Academy Team|publisher=|accessdate=7 February 2016}}</ref> The team was launched in November 2014 by a team with the aim of developing young cyclists, especially from Israel.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gallery: Sagan helps launch first Israeli pro team|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/gallery-sagan-helps-launch-first-israeli-pro-team|accessdate=9 May 2015|work=[[Cyclingnews.com]]|date=26 November 2014}}</ref>

The team's first ever victory came in the fourth stage of the [[2015 Tour d'Azerbaïdjan]], which was won by [[Daniel Turek]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Tour d'Azerbaïdjan 2015 – Stage 4|url=http://procyclingstats.com/race/Tour_d_Azerbaidjan_2015_Stage_4_Mingachevir|website=ProCyclingStats|accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref>

On 2 July 2015, the team announced that it added the Israeli Road Racing Champion [[Guy Sagiv]] to its ranks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Twitter: Cycling Academy adds Guy Sagiv|url=https://twitter.com/bikeGEEEEKS/statuses/61662535119668428|work=[[twitter.com]]|date=2 July 2015|accessdate=24 August 2015}}</ref>

In 2018 the team participated in a [[Cycling monument]] event for the first time – [[2018 Milan-San Remo]], and in a [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tour]] event for the first time – [[2018 Giro d'Italia]].

