'''Rhys Palmer''' (born 22 January 1996) is a professional [[cricket]]er who plays for [[Jersey cricket team|Jersey]].<ref name="Bio">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/470894.html |title=Rhys Palmer |accessdate=21 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> He played in the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Five]] tournament<ref name="DivFive">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/979811.html |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Five, Jersey v Oman at St Saviour, May 21, 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> and the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] matches held in Los Angeles. In August 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018–19 ICC World Twenty20 Europe Qualifier]] tournament in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/45171461 |title=Jersey name squad for World Twenty20 first-round qualifier |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/808096 |title=Three debutants in Jersey squad for ICC World T20 Europe Qualifier |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref>

